			<div class="content" id="post-content-4217376">
									

<p><span style="font-size:large;"><strong>EDIT: THIS IS NOW A <a href="/k-class-complete-list">COLLABORATIVE PAGE</a>!!!. Have at, folks!</strong></span></p>
<p>It seems like we've had a proliferation<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-47338-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-47338-1')">1</a></sup> of K-class discussion posts lately. It's been a while since anyone went through and looked at actual usage, so I decided to do this. Note: I'm writing this after staring at a screen for&#8230; oh, 3 hours? So I'm a little punchy. Edited 4-13 to add DoomsCon.</p>
<p><strong>Methodology</strong></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li>This only includes SCPs and -001 proposals tagged <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/system:page-tags/tag/k-class-scenario#pages">k-class-scenario</a> as of 4-10-19, excluding jokes</li>
<li>No tales, no GOI formats - Sorry, I only had time to use the tag.</li>
<li>No apocryphal forum posts, no sandbox links, no TVTropes pages. Just actual usage in SCPs
<ul>
<li>I based my definitions on the gist of the predominance of articles. I do not care if these match definitions in any other lists. Usage!</li>
<li>The number in the list includes inconsistent entries.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>I don't actually know how to data scrape, so this is all manual.
<ul>
<li>I searched for k-class, scenario, event, &quot;k &quot;, or just visually scanned if none of that worked</li>
<li>I tried to get all collapsibles and offsets (and checked page source), but I might've missed something.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Edit: DoomsCon get their own list, taken from the hub.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>A bit on notation:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>&quot;K-class <em>scenario</em>&quot; and &quot;K-class <em>event</em>&quot; seem to be used interchangeably, I can't find any consistent logic to it. Scenario was used 179 times in my list and event was used 47 times.</li>
<li>Capitalization (XK-Class End&#8230;, XK-class end&#8230;) and truncation (end-of-the-world, &quot;end of the world&quot;, end of the world) don't seem to have any set standard.</li>
</ul>
